OL,3,CRailway worker knocked down by train
OL,4,Ctravelling too fast, report finds
OL,6,FFollowing the investigation, the RAIB
OL,7,Fmade two recommendations to GWR.
OL,9,F1. Review the personal track safety
OL,10,Ftraining and assessment it provides
OL,11,Ffor shunters, so that they receive an
OL,12,Fappropriate level of information and
OL,13,Fassessment about working and walking
OL,14,Fon depots.
OL,16,F2. Identify the places on its depots
OL,17,Fwhere its staff might be required to
OL,18,Fwalk foul of a train's path when using
OL,19,Fa walking route or walkway, and then
OL,20,Fmanage the risk of its staff being
OL,21,Fstruck by a train in these locations.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/9
